    <h1>Weakest Preconditions in Fibrations</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Bart Jacobs · 2014 · <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/1412.6"; class="inline">preprint</a></p>

    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Prereqs: <a href="/reading/natural-breadcrumbs/staton-2025/">🍞 Staton 2025</a> (Hoare triples, weakest precondition). <a href="/reading/natural-breadcrumbs/fritz-2020/">🍞 Fritz 2020</a> (Kleisli categories) helps.</p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Weakest preconditions arise automatically from a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fibred_category"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>fibration</a> over a Kleisli category. The poset of predicates sitting above each type is the fiber; lifting a morphism through the fibration computes wp.</p>
    </div>

